<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Da Lat</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[French colonial hill station at 1,500 m. Crazy House (Hằng Nga Guesthouse) is a tree-shaped surrealist hotel by the architect daughter of a former Vietnamese president. Cog-railway to Trai Mat village (5 km).]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.458300,11.940400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Prenn Pass</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Top of the descent off the plateau. View south over the Don Duong reservoir; pine forests give way to deciduous tropical species lower down.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.381400,11.762500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bao Loc</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Tea and silk country. Roadside dragon-fruit plantations from here southward — Vietnam is the world's largest producer.]]></description><Point><coordinates>107.805600,11.543600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Phan Thiet</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Fish-sauce capital. Centuries-old factories along the river. Cham towers at Po Sah Inu (8th century) remind you that this coast was Cham territory before Vietnamese expansion southward absorbed it in the 17th century.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.092500,10.948300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mui Ne fishing village</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Round basket-boats (thúng chai) bring in fish each morning. Sunrise on the harbor with hundreds of these strange wickerwork bowls is one of Vietnam's iconic sights.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.284200,10.933300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mui Ne red dunes</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Surreal red dunes against blue sea — sand sledding for kids, photographs for adults. Best at sunrise/sunset; midday the sand is too hot to walk on.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.297800,10.941900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bau Trang white dunes</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Larger and whiter than the red dunes; quad bikes for hire. Lotus pond at the base flowers May–August.]]></description><Point><coordinates>108.425300,10.945600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
